Create /Load Dimension and Fact Tables from ODS 10

Step 1: Create ConsumerComplaint_DW environment by downloading   and unzip the SQL Script to create tables in the Datawarehouse Area:

 Go to SQL Server Management Studio and use the SQL Script to create your DW Database and tables. This creates all the tables. Run the script below in Management Studio:

  •          ConsumerComplaints-CreateDW20210604.sql

Confirm in Management Studio that the objects have been created by right clicking on the Database tab and selecting Refresh. Then run script provided to create all the table objects.  See below Screen:

       


Step 2: Create SSIS Packages to load the Dimension Tables

 Go to Visual Studio:

       1.    Create New SSIS package _ Rename Package as 0.3_ LoadDimTables.dtsx

1.               2.       Use Connection Managers to create :

                    - Connection for OLE DB Source >>> ConsumerComplaints_ODS

                    - Connection for OLE DB Destination >>> ConsumerComplaints_DW

        

              3.  Click and drag the Execute SQL Task on the designer pane

                     - Rename the Execute SQL Task as EST_ DimComplainantINFO

                     - Configure the Execute SQL Task Editor to connect to ConsumerComplaints_DW Database

                     - In the SQL Statement  write Execute [dbo]. [usp_DimComplainantINFO]

                

                 

               

             

-          -  Execute Task  ( Execute [dbo]. [usp_DimComplainantINFO])

               

            

                  - Repeat the step 3 to execute the other SP that will load the remaining  Dimension tables

                   ·       Dim_Complaints

·       Dim_Company

·       Dim_TypeOfIssue

·       Dim_Location

·       Dim_Product

·       Dim_Date  [ We will need to pass the Start and End date to execute the SP]

[Execute [dbo].[uspDimCalendarDay] '01/01/2011','12/31/2021']

                  

              

               Step 3: Create SSIS Packages to load the Fact Tables

    Go to Visual Studio:

       1.    Create New SSIS package _ Rename Package as 0.4_ LoadFactTables.dtsx

1.               2.       Use Connection Managers to create :

                    - Connection for OLE DB Source >>> ConsumerComplaints_ODS

                    - Connection for OLE DB Destination >>> ConsumerComplaints_DW

        

              3.  Click and drag the Data Flow Task on the designer pane

                     - Rename the Data Flow Task as DFT_ Load FactComplaintDetails

                     - The package is then build to load the Fact table from ODS database as shown below                           

             

             

                Step 4: Create SSIS Packages to load the First Fact Tables

    1.  Click and drag OLE DB Source >> Rename as OLE DB_ConsumerComplaints_ODS,          Configure the Editor to connect to ODS database and select tbl_ConsumerComplaints_ODS table                                                                        

      


  2.   Click and drag Lookup Transformation Task >>[Rename LookupDataKey]

         Configure the Lookup Transformation Editor as follows:

        General       Cache mode >> Select Full cache

                                 Connection type >> Select OLEDB connection manger

                    Specify how to handle rows with no matching entries

                               >> Select Redirect rows to no matching output

       Connection   OLE DB connection manager:

                            >> Select ServerName.ComsumerComplaints_DW

                           Use a table or a view >> Select the [dbo].[Dim_Date]  to Lookup DateKey

    Columns  >> Select [Tick] DateKey Connect a least one matching record from the “Available Input Columns” to the “Available Lookup Columns”  >>>Then click OK

    

    Click and drag new Lookup Task >> connect the Lookup together selecting “Lookup Match Output

Repeat the above steps to configure the Lookup Task for the following Lookup

3.        ProductKey       [Dim_Product]

4.        IssueKey           [Dim_TypeOfIssue]

5.        ComplaintKey   [Dim_Complaints]

6.        CompanyKey     [Dim_Company]

7.        LocationKey      [Dim_Location]

8.     Click and drag Derived Column Transformation Task on to the designer pane, connect it and create the columns    

         -         CreatedBy

   -         ModifiedBy

 9.    Click and drag the OLE DB Destination. Rename as OLE DB                                                                              Destination_FactComplaintDetails and connect to Derived Column -  Configure it as shown below and run the entire package

2.   Set up the Lookup Transformation as shown below


3.   Set up the Lookup Transformation as shown below

 Run the Package
